                    <state type="martyr" source="#bib1791-2">
                        <p>Martyr</p>
                    </state>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1791">In hagiography: <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1791">Isaac, bishop of Karka</persName> was a bishop of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/108">Karka d-Beth Slokh</placeName> who was martyred under <persName>Shapor II</persName> along with <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1450">Shapor, bishop of Niqator</persName>. Their names was later associated with a group of martyrs killed under <persName>Yazdgerd II</persName> including <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1354">Maʿna</persName>, <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1110">Abraham</persName>, and <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1474">Simeon</persName>.  </note>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1791-1" source="#bib1791-1">
                        <p xml:lang="en">
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1791">Isaac, bishop of Karka</persName> is commemorated in <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/261">Shapor, Isaac, Maʿna, Abraham and Simeon (text)</title>.</p>
                    </event>
